  <content:encoded><![CDATA[The BSIMM metrics were created to figure out a good standing point for people to strive for security. The BSIMM team observed 67 well known companies and their personal security initiatives in order to come up with a model that showed people not what they should be doing or what the best practice invovoling software security is, but where they stand in relation to the average of the top. Because of the approach that the BSIMM team took, it's much easier for companies to look at what they're doing and see if they match up to the 112 security activities.]]></content:encoded>
