  <content:encoded><![CDATA[We are a team of 6 ASU seniors that have been tasked with creating an internal facing web application which will monitor Infusionsoft's security policies and metrics and compare them to the Building Security in Maturity Model (BSIMM). We decided to tackle this task by using agile programming methodologies, specially scrum, as we felt the frequent meetings through tri-weeklyÂ stand-ups and constant creation of a completed product suited our needs perfectly.

At the start we decided that we would meet with our Infusionsoft sponsors once every two weeks for our sprint retrospective and FIX ME CANT THINK OF WORD and they would call in on one of our tri-weekly stand-up meetings each week. This would maximize our facetime with them while allowing them to be disengaged from the project to act as product owners and also not take away too much time from their own work, as they are employees of Infusionsoft and this is a side project.]]></content:encoded>
